      },
      "module": "motivation",
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "Keyword: loop primitives",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The taxonomy provides a treatment of **context compaction** -- the techniques (summarisation, truncation, selective retention, hierarchical rollups) that coding agents use to fit their working context into the underlying model's bounded window as a session grows.",
